> Hey presto! These speedy Pronto Italian Style Sausage Meatballs are ready in under 25 minutes. Using herby oregano sausage meat makes the meatballs come together quickly to save time but still make a dinner that's full of flavour.

== Mash ==

Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a full #kettle{}.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (peel first if you prefer).

Pour the boiling water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp}.

Add the potatoes to the water and cook until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{15-18%minutes}.

== Meatballs ==

In the meantime, roll the @British Pork and Oregano Sausage Meat{225%g} into even-sized balls, 5 per person.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Pop the meatballs onto a #baking tray{} and, when the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until browned on the outside and cooked through, ~{10-12%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The meatballs are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Pesto Tomato Sauce ==

While everything cooks, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the garlic and fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @Tomato Passata{1%carton}, @Mixed Herbs{1%sachet}, @Chicken Stock Paste{10%g}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @water{100%ml}(for the sauce). Bring the sauce to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened slightly, ~{4-5%minutes}.

== Mash Finish ==

Once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan, off the heat.

Add a knob of @butter{}(knob) and a splash of @?milk{}(splash) and mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth.

Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Cover with a #lid{} to keep warm.

== Assembly ==

Once your sauce has thickened, stir through the @peas{120%g} and cook for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Meanwhile, grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{30%g}(grated).

Add the @Pesto{32%g} to the sauce and mix until well combined, then add the cooked meatballs and stir to coat.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} if needed. Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

Share the mash between your bowls.

Top with the Italian style meatballs and sauce.

Sprinkle over the cheese to finish.

Enjoy!